value.value: Terminology associated with the standard name codelist of the Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC) Define-XML standard.
A tablet exhibiting an altered inherent rate of release of active and/or inert ingredient(s).

A standard document developed and maintained by Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC) that contains instructions and requirements for the organization, structure, and format of standard clinical and non-clinical trial tabulation and analysis datasets.
The implementation guide for the CDISC Study Data Tabulation Model standard.
The implementation guide for the CDISC Standard for the Exchange of Nonclinical Data standard.
The total volume of gas in a specified airway or set of airways at a specified point in time in the respiratory cycle.
A carcinoma that arises from the pancreas, bile ducts, gallbladder, or ampulla of Vater and has spread from its original site of growth to another anatomic site.
A carcinoma that arises from the pancreas, bile ducts, gallbladder, or ampulla of Vater and has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes.

The degree or grade of excellence with respect to medical services received by patients, administered by providers or programs, in terms of technical competence, need, appropriateness, acceptability, humanity and structure.

label.value: Locally Advanced Malignant Female Reproductive System Neoplasm

value.value: A malignant female reproductive system neoplasm that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes.
Endometrial carcinoma that has spread to nearby tissues or lymph nodes.
Gallbladder carcinoma that has spread to nearby tissues or lymph nodes.
A term that refers to the decrease in the cancer size and extend of metastases, and/or lymph node involvement by cancer, to a lower (less extensive) stage.
Skin squamous cell carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.
Skin carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.
A regimen consisting of dexamethasone, isatuximab and pomalidomide that can be used for the treatment of plasma cell (multiple) myeloma.

label.value: Metastatic Malignant Head and Neck Neoplasm

value.value: A malignant neoplasm that arises from the head and neck region and has spread to another anatomic site.

label.value: Advanced Malignant Head and Neck Neoplasm

value.value: A malignant neoplasm that arises from the head and neck region and has spread extensively to other anatomic sites or is no longer responding to treatment.

The subjective measurement of an individual's sense of well-being and ability to enjoy life. The concept holds varying meanings for different people and may evolve over time. For some individuals it implies autonomy, empowerment, capability, and choice; for others, security, social integration, or freedom from stress or illness.

label.value: Locally Advanced Malignant Head and Neck Neoplasm

value.value: A malignant neoplasm that arises from the head and neck region and has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes.
Diminished mental function after chemotherapy.

label.value: Skin Atypical Lipomatous Tumor/Well Differentiated Liposarcoma

value.value: A rare atypical lipomatous tumor/well differentiated liposarcoma arising from the skin.
A rare pleomorphic liposarcoma arising from the skin.
A spindle cell/pleomorphic lipoma arising from the skin.
A spindle cell lipoma arising from the skin.
A pleomorphic lipoma arising from the skin.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of the PRKD2 gene.
An angiolipoma arising from the skin.
A predetermined set of questions.
A geographic ancestral origin category that is assigned to a population group based mainly on physical characteristics that are thought to be distinct and inherent.
A numeric representation of the collected amount of time during which an activity or observation continues.
The unit of measure for the collected time duration.
A sequence of characters used to uniquely identify a fetus associated with a maternal subject, for a particular prenatal evaluation.

The nominal study day, relative to the sponsor-defined reference start date, used by data-collection and reporting systems for grouping records for observations that may be scheduled to occur on different days into a single study day (e.g., for output on a tabulation report).
The name for a protocol-defined nominal study day.

A biphenyl matrix metalloproteinase (MMP) inhibitor (MMPI) with potential antineoplastic activity. Tanomastat inhibits MMP-2, MMP-3, and MMP-9, inhibiting extracellular matrix degradation and potentially inhibiting angiogenesis, tumor growth and invasion, and metastasis. MMPs consist of at least 18 zinc-containing endo-proteinases that are capable of degrading collagen and proteoglycan.
The radiation of energy as transverse waves produced by moving charges.
Anatomical location where the result was observed.

label.value: Date Time of Last Study Treatment

value.value: The end date or date and time of the last exposure to any protocol-specified treatment or therapy, represented in a standardized character format.

label.value: Date Time of First Study Treatment

value.value: The start date or date and time of the first exposure to any protocol-specified treatment or therapy, represented in a standardized character format.
A short sequence of characters that represents the planned reproductive path to which the subject was assigned.

label.value: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation

value.value: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation occurred.

label.value: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End

value.value: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation ended.

label.value: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation

value.value: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to occur.

label.value: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation End

value.value: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to end.

label.value: Planned Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start

value.value: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation was scheduled to begin.

label.value: Actual Reproductive Phase Day of Observation Start

value.value: The day within the reproductive phase on which the test or observation began.

The ability of some cells or tissues to withstand ionizing radiation without serious injury. Tolerance depends on the species, cell type, and physical and chemical variables, including RADIATION-PROTECTIVE AGENTS and RADIATION-SENSITIZING AGENTS.
An indication or description that the performed test or observation was done at a time that was not preplanned.
A rare developmental anomaly characterized by the presence of ectopic adipose tissue within the upper half of the dermis. (WHO 2018)
